         <abstract>
            <p>In the present paper a necessary condition for a cyclic extension of the rationals of prime degree $l$ to have an integral normal basis generated by a unit is given. For a fixed $l$, this condition implies that there exists at most a finite number of such fields. A computational method for verifying the existence of an integral normal basis generated by a unit is given. For $l = 5$, all such fields are found.</p>
          </abstract>
